  "datePublished": "2020-12-05",
  "description": "This post has to do with computer technology, and the intersection of that technology with other contemporary technologies, like mechanisms of settler-colonialism.\nIn this post, I’m going to name names. These problems are social and cultural, but both of those things are made by people. Despite all the things I’m about to say about the people I’m about to talk about, I want to make it clear, I have a lot of respect for them. They are, all of them, willing to do hard and often thankless work, based on nothing more than a promise they made to themselves about their role in life. Brought up with a different set of knowledge and experience, these people might have grown up to become an inspiration for me. And as people, their knowledge and experience isn’t set in stone: any of these people might go on to become inspirational.\n",
  "name": "False profits",
